    "text_excerpt": "Homepage - Natalie Bennett Green Party Peer #NatalieGreenPeer Latest About About Natalie Publications Podcasts Events Other Roles Green Thinking Unlearning Outdated Ideas in Science, Economics and Politics “A powerful and timely call to rethink how we understand progress, knowledge and our place in the natural world. Written with clarity, courage and hope, Green Thinking challenges assumptions and inspires new ways of seeing the future.” Peter Frankopan Find out about this book Change Everything setting out Green political philosophy ‘Every so often, a book comes along that articulates exactly what our country needs. This is one. Essential reading’ Zack Polanski Find out about this book Facebook Twitter Instagram TikTok Comments Box SVG icons Used for the like, share, comment, and reaction icons Natalie Bennett, Green Party Member of the House of Lords Natalie Bennett, Green Party Member of the House of Lords 3 days ago The UK does not have national food stockpiles or plans to create these! 🤦‍♀️ … See More See Less View on Facebook &middot; Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Linked In Share by Email View Comments likes love haha sad 37 Shares: 3 Comments: 6 6 Comments Comment on Facebook Natalie Bennett, Green Party Member of the House of Lords is in Hamburg, Germany. 4 days ago What does integrated transport look like? Now if they could just manage an integrated sign for the buses at least at Victoria station…. … See More See Less View on Facebook &middot; Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Linked In Share by Email View Comments likes love 49 Shares: 2 Comments: 8 8 Comments Comment on Facebook Natalie Bennett, Green Party Member of the House of Lords 4 days ago Glad to see that my favourite Chinese restaurant is still in Cologne railway station, and still serving food on proper plates with proper cutlery. Amazing what a bit of political will can achieve for a #circulareconomy … See More See Less View on Facebook &middot; Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Linked In Share by Email View Comments likes love 46 Shares: 1 Comments: 6 6 Comments Comment on Facebook Load more Natalie Bennett Follow 126,478 171,891 Retweet on Twitter Natalie Bennett Retweeted Zack Polanski @ZackPolanski &middot; 16h 2050619408066757049 It’s Greens Vs Labour/Reform/Tories. Pick your side. Join the Green Party Join the Green Party from just £6 a year. Become a member today – join the only party standing up for people and planet Join.greenparty.org.uk Reply on Twitter 2050619408066757049 Retweet on Twitter 2050619408066757049 798 Like on Twitter 2050619408066757049 5042 X 2050619408066757049 Natalie Bennett @natalieben &middot; 15h 2050624039861825820 #IndustrialAgriculture – so many costs “Contamination is also the result of a historical accumulation that should lead us to more broadly rethink intensive, monoculture-based agriculture” ‘Public health time bomb’: How France allowed cadmium to poison its crops and soil French residents are three to four times more likely to register unsafe levels of cadmium in their bodies than t… www.france24.com Reply on Twitter 2050624039861825820 Retweet on Twitter 2050624039861825820 7 Like on Twitter 2050624039861825820 9 X 2050624039861825820 Natalie Bennett @natalieben &middot; 17h 2050606415257952371 Useful reflection: “in treating human innovation as solution to all humanity’s problems, it fails to acknowledge that many of those problems exist because of human inventions, not (as in Project Hail Mary) light-eating space microbes” ‘Project Hail Mary’ and the Politics of Science Fiction Even the most entertaining tale carries a political message. foreignpolicy.com Reply on Twitter 2050606415257952371 Retweet on Twitter 2050606415257952371 2 Like on Twitter 2050606415257952371 11 X 2050606415257952371 Load More nataliebennettgreen 3,240 9,541 The UK does not have national food stockpiles or plans to create these! 🤦‍♀️ 30 4 Open post by nataliebennettgreen with ID 1799",
